3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222848%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jennifer%20Sisson%20headshot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a5cb9e4cc8540019cb7e1f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221424%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Jennifer%20Sisson.%3Cp%3EJennifer%20Sisson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20always%20saved%20slowly%2C%20planning%20to%20retire%20at%2065.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThen%2C%20FIRE%20taught%20us%20that%20retirement%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20triggered%20by%20an%20age%2C%20but%20by%20a%20sum.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20we're%20saving%20%241.2%20million%20and%20investing%20in%20real%20estate%20to%20retire%20early.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20started%20our%20retirement%20savings%20like%20most%20people%20do%3A%20we%20contributed%20to%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%3E401(k)s%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20didn't%20know%20what%20we%20were%20doing%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20we%20just%20knew%20we%20needed%20to%20be%20investing%20so%20we'd%20have%20a%20nest%20egg%20in%20our%20golden%20years.%20We%20started%20with%20target%20date%20funds%20and%20then%20%26quot%3Bgraduated%26quot%3B%20to%20a%20broad%20mix%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmutual-funds%5C%22%3Emutual%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20also%20started%20contributing%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20feeling%20very%20proud%20of%20ourselves.%20Our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20grew%20slowly%20as%20we%20got%20our%204%25%20company%20match%2C%20and%20we%20contributed%20a%20little%20extra%20when%20money%20allowed.%20If%20we%20continued%20to%20truck%20along%20at%20the%20same%20rate%2C%20we'd%20have%20enough%20for%20a%20comfy%20retirement%20around%20age%2065.%20That%20was%20as%20far%20as%20our%20frame%20of%20reference%20allowed%20us%20to%20see%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20discovered%20the%20FIRE%20(financial%20independence%2C%20retire%20early)%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDown%20the%20FIRE%20rabbit%20hole%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20books%20and%20podcasts%20introduced%20me%20to%20this%20new%20concept%3A%20Retirement%20wasn't%20an%20age%20but%20a%20number%20%E2%80%94%20an%20amount%20of%20money%20large%20enough%20that%20you%20could%20live%20on%20the%20interest%20it%20produced%20without%20touching%20the%20principal.%20With%20this%20lump%20sum%20as%20a%20money-generating%20machine%2C%20we%20could%20be%20financially%20independent%2C%20no%20longer%20need%20a%20job%2C%20and%20be%20ready%20to%20retire.%20And%20if%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20could%20get%20to%20that%20number%20faster%2C%20we%20could%20quit%20working%20sooner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20made%20a%20tentative%20goal%20of%20%241.2%20million.%20According%20to%20the%20oft-cited%20Trinity%20Study%20(which%20is%20essentially%20canon%20scripture%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-independence-retire-early%5C%22%3EFIRE%20movement%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20you%20can%20withdraw%204%25%20of%20a%20stock%20portfolio%20each%20year%20and%20not%20eat%20into%20the%20principal.%20Stocks%20tend%20to%20appreciate%20more%20than%20this%20(around%207%25)%2C%20but%20the%20so-called%204%25%20rule%20keeps%20withdrawals%20low%20enough%20to%20account%20for%20bull%20market%20years%20when%20your%20portfolio%20is%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20rule%20helped%20us%20reverse-engineer%20how%20big%20our%20nest%20egg%20needed%20to%20be.%20We're%20pretty%20frugal%20folks%2C%20so%20we%20figured%20we%20could%20live%20on%20around%20%2448%2C000%20in%20retirement%2C%20which%20is%204%25%20of%20%241.2%20million.%20We%20were%20ignited%20by%20our%20new%20focus%2C%20but%20%241.2%20million%20was%20a%20very%20distant%20goal.%20We%20earned%20enough%20for%20our%20needs%2C%20but%20we%20didn't%20have%20the%20latitude%20to%20ramp%20up%20our%209-to-5%20income%20to%20save%20more%20aggressively%20than%20we%20already%20were.%20So%2C%20we%20started%20brainstorming%20other%20ways%20to%20hit%20our%20goal%20sooner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20shift%20from%20stocks%20to%20real%20estate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20hadn't%20dabbled%20in%20the%20FIRE%20community%20long%20before%20we%20came%20across%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-real-estate-investing-platforms%5C%22%3Ereal%20estate%20investing%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20avenue%20to%20hit%20our%20retirement%20number%20earlier.%20We%20had%20an%20interest%20in%20owning%20rentals%20even%20before%20we%20discovered%20FIRE.%20After%20some%20back-of-the-napkin%20math%2C%20we%20realized%20that%20this%20could%20be%20the%20shortcut%20we%20were%20looking%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20rental%20properties%2C%20we%20realized%20we%20didn't%20need%20the%20whole%20%241.2%20million%20sitting%20in%20a%20retirement%20account%3B%20we%20just%20needed%20%2448%2C000%20a%20year%20(or%20%244%2C000%20a%20month)%20in%20cash%20flow.%20If%20we%20could%20make%20%24200%20in%20monthly%20profit%20per%20rental%20unit%2C%20we%20were%2020%20doors%20away%20from%20retiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20alluring%20aspect%20of%20real%20estate%20was%20that%20elements%20of%20the%20investment%20were%20under%20our%20direct%20control.%20With%20stocks%2C%20we%20bought%20and%20crossed%20our%20fingers%2C%20hoping%20they'd%20go%20up%20over%20time.%20With%20a%20rental%2C%20we%20could%20renovate%20the%20house%20to%20%3Cem%3Emake%20%3C%2Fem%3Eits%20value%20go%20up.%20Plus%2C%20nicer%20units%20would%20command%20higher%20rents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20we%20could%20take%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-mortgage-lenders%5C%22%3Emortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20purchase%20properties%2C%20whereas%20we%20had%20to%20rely%20solely%20on%20our%20own%20money%20for%20saving%20in%20our%20401(k).%20That%20leverage%20could%20help%20us%20acquire%20more%20assets%20than%20we%20could%20on%20our%20own.%20After%20we%20retired%2C%20we'd%20also%20have%20our%20pick%20of%20the%20properties%20to%20live%20in%2C%20should%20we%20ever%20need%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20in%20mind%2C%20we%20started%20purchasing%20rentals.%20We've%20acquired%20two%20so%20far.%20One%20surpassed%20our%20expectations.%20We%20ran%20it%20as%20a%20profitable%20Airbnb%20for%20a%20while%20before%20converting%20it%20to%20a%20hands-off%20long-term%20rental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20was%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20bust%20%E2%80%94%20a%20rehab%20that%20took%20longer%20and%20cost%20more%20than%20anticipated.%20The%20cash%20flow%20came%20short%20of%20our%20goal%20of%20%24200%20per%20door%2C%20but%20the%20success%20of%20our%20first%20property%20has%20offset%20the%20shortcomings%20of%20the%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20balanced%20approach%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20building%20up%20our%20real%20estate%20portfolio%2C%20we've%20continued%20to%20save%20in%20our%20401(k)%20and%20Roth%20IRA%20accounts.%20There%20are%20no%20guarantees%20in%20investing%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20want%20all%20of%20our%20proverbial%20eggs%20in%20the%20real%20estate%20basket.%20If%20my%20husband%20or%20I%20become%20unable%20to%20fix%20up%20houses%20or%20the%20housing%20market%20experiences%20another%202008-style%20crash%2C%20we%20want%20our%20stock%20portfolio%20as%20a%20backup%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20retiring%20on%20time%20isn't%20a%20bad%20backup%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3