0of%20Marathi%20language%20books%20with%20us.%20My%20mother%20and%20sister%20did%20not%20know%20much%20beyond%20farming%2C%20so%20they%20started%20a%20makeshift%20tea%20stall%20to%20meet%20our%20expenses%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENo%20phones%2C%20only%20books!%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20Bhimabai%2C%20along%20with%20her%20daughter%2C%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20what%20is%20today%20Ajjichya%20Pustakancha%20Hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20family%20moved%2C%20the%20taunts%20and%20harsh%20words%20never%20stopped%20following%20her.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20would%20talk%20about%20how%20the%20women%20of%20the%20house%20should%20not%20wander%20around%20selling%20tea%3B%20she%20should%20take%20care%20of%20the%20house.%20But%20I%20did%20not%20care%20about%20those%20taunts%20anymore%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20children%20and%20I%20slowly%20started%20to%20use%20savings%20to%20expand%20the%20tea%20stall%20and%20make%20it%20an%20eatery.%20What%20I%20noticed%20was%20that%20while%20a%20person%20would%20wait%20for%20their%20food%2C%20they%20would%20always%20be%20buried%20in%20their%20phone%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20would%20not%20converse%20with%20each%20other%20but%20would%20keep%20scrolling%20on%20their%20phone.%20I%20found%20the%20habit%20very%20absurd%20and%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20woman%20who%20was%20fond%20of%20reading%20but%20never%20got%20the%20chance%20to%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20reintroduce%20the%20habit%20of%20reading%20to%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBooks%20are%20our%20best%20friends.%20They%20are%20your%20companions%20in%20every%20situation.%20We%20started%20off%20with%20just%2025%20books%20in%20a%20stand%20in%20the%20eatery%20and%20it%20kept%20growing.%20We%20started%20encouraging%20people%20to%20pick%20up%20a%20book%20and%20read%20while%20